    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:30.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Claim\nConnect becomes a bridge: drives pulled from Switchboard via GQL are simultaneously mirrored to Swarm storage, so users can migrate gradually.\n\n## Evidence\nFrom the source: \"Connect becomes a bridge between the existing Switchboard ecosystem and the decentralized Swarm network. Any remote drive from Switchboard can be automatically mirrored to Swarm storage.\"\n\nThe bridge diagram shows Remote Drives (A, B) pulled via GQL and pushed out via Swarm, alongside Local Drives (C) that live only on Swarm.\n\n## Consequences\n- Users can disconnect from Switchboard after mirroring completes.\n- Both remote and local drives become recoverable on any device via Swarm.\n- No data is locked into a single infrastructure.\n\n## Source\nSwarm Channel Architecture, \"The Bridge Pattern\" diagram.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:30.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:30.000Z"
    }
  },
